while creating  docker image and running CA.

First we need dockerfile.In dockerfile we need dockerfile instructions

🔹 Build-time instructions  (executes at the time of image creation) :-FROM,RUN,COPY,ADD,WOKDIR,LABEL,ARG

🔹 Runtime instructions:CMD,ENTRYPOINT,ENV,USER,EXPOSE,HEALTHCHECK

🔹 RUN : RUN instruction is used for to installing packages ,doing some configurations e.t.c .
         RUN executes at the time of image creation
         In dockerfile there can have N of RUN instructions.

          From almalinux:9
          RUN dnf install nginx -y

🔹 CMD : CMD excutes at the time of CA creation.Nothing but at the time of docker run.
         There should be only one CMD in dockerfile
 
           CMD = default command at container start


  Note :  RUN VS CMD :
          1.RUN execute at time of image creation.We can use multiple run inst in dockerfile due to like we need install multiple packages ect.
           2.CMD execute at the time of container creation.We can execute only one CMD in docker file.

🔹 COPY :copy instruction is used to copy the code from local to container.

🔹 ADD :copy and add both are used for copies the code from local to CA.but add  has 2 advantages
         1.it can directly fetch the file from internet
         2.it can directly untar the file from CA.


🔹 Label :It nothing but a tag in aws.it will help at the time of filtering

          LABEL COURSE="Devops" \
                NAER="narendra" \
                Time="1month" \

The above is syntax for using multiple lables.

🔹 MAINTAINER : The MAINTAINER instruction in a Dockerfile was originally used to specify who maintains the image.
 
              FROM almalinux:9
        LABEL COURSE="Devops" \
        NAME="narendra" \
        Time="1month" \
        maintainer="bijilinariit@gmail.com"

