🔹 **EXPOSE :**The EXPOSE instruction in a Dockerfile is used to document which port your container listens on at runtime.(Purely for documentation purpose)
The EXPOSE instruction doesn't actually publish the port. It functions as a type of documentation between the person who builds the image and the person who runs the container, about which ports are intended to be published.
🔹 ENV : The ENV instruction in a Dockerfile is used to set environment variables inside the container.
🔹 Entrypoint : CMD inst can be override.
                we can't override Entrypint.if we try to do it will upend.
                we can use both combination for better results .Entry point will have command and default arguments supplied by CMD.
we can always override default args through command line

